WEBVTT

00:02.381 --> 00:03.486
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.520 --> 00:04.970
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.455 --> 00:10.355
♪ I don't care what you say!

00:11.701 --> 00:14.014
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:14.048 --> 00:16.257
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:16.292 --> 00:18.190
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:18.225 --> 00:22.643
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:32.411 --> 00:34.586
Nnyeh.
Wow.

00:36.622 --> 00:38.038
Look at that tank top!

00:38.072 --> 00:39.349
Hn?

00:39.384 --> 00:41.455
Hey Clarence, why don't you take
a look in the backyard?

00:41.489 --> 00:42.904
Hey, I've got
something for -- oh!

00:42.939 --> 00:45.976
Ms. Mushburger.
-Mary. I brought you new book.

00:46.011 --> 00:48.048
Oh, come on in, I guess.
[ Laughs nervously ]

00:48.082 --> 00:49.911
Book club's not for a couple
weeks, not that I...

00:49.946 --> 00:51.361
-Hmm...
-...need a couple weeks.

00:51.396 --> 00:52.776
That's not why I'm here.

00:52.811 --> 00:53.881
Okay.

00:53.915 --> 00:56.780
I'm going to my friend's
art opening in Utah.

00:56.815 --> 00:58.230
Ooh.
That sounds like fun.

00:58.265 --> 01:01.095
Her paintings are a nightmarish
depiction of the horrors

01:01.130 --> 01:03.649
that accompany
solitary confinement.

01:03.684 --> 01:06.307
Anyway, I'm expecting
some important packages

01:06.342 --> 01:09.103
while I'm away, and I don't
want them to be stolen.

01:09.138 --> 01:11.657
You're right next-door,
so, if you see any packages,

01:11.692 --> 01:13.003
would you please
take them inside?

01:13.038 --> 01:15.109
You sure got a lot
of keys here, heh heh.

01:15.144 --> 01:17.974
These keys unlock
more than doors.

01:18.008 --> 01:21.288
Except this one with the red
cover, it unlocks my front door.

01:21.322 --> 01:22.496
Can I have this?

01:22.530 --> 01:23.945
All right! You should
probably go now!

01:23.980 --> 01:24.981
Oh! Wow!

01:25.015 --> 01:27.294
Are you practicing
for the cirque?

01:27.328 --> 01:29.123
[ Grunting ]

01:29.158 --> 01:30.435
Whew.

01:30.469 --> 01:32.678
Oh. My. Goodness.

01:32.713 --> 01:35.336
A trampoliiiiiiiiiine!

01:35.371 --> 01:37.338
♪♪

01:37.373 --> 01:40.341
I love it I love it I love it
I love it I love it!

01:40.376 --> 01:42.412
Well, enjoy your child.

01:42.447 --> 01:43.862
I'll be back Sunday.

01:43.896 --> 01:45.657
Don't forget
the packages.

01:45.691 --> 01:46.865
Tood-A-Loo.

01:46.899 --> 01:48.418
Thanks, Mom, I love it!

01:48.453 --> 01:50.144
Oh! I love
this trampoline.

01:50.179 --> 01:51.318
[ Laughs ]

01:51.352 --> 01:54.355
Mom...is that lady...
a witch?

01:54.390 --> 01:56.495
What? No.

01:56.530 --> 01:58.048
Well, she does...

01:58.083 --> 01:59.360
witchy stuff...

01:59.395 --> 02:00.637
and her house...

02:00.672 --> 02:03.364
looks like a witch house...
for sure.

02:03.399 --> 02:05.021
Clarence,
she's just creative.

02:05.055 --> 02:07.851
Yeah, but what about
that one book club?

02:09.405 --> 02:11.131
[ Guttural chewing ]

02:11.165 --> 02:12.511
Okay, that was weird.

02:12.546 --> 02:15.307
But come on, you guys don't
believe in witches, do you?

02:15.342 --> 02:18.621
[ Haunting music plays ]

02:18.655 --> 02:20.692
I'm gonna go watch a "Blurbs"
marathon on the TV.

02:20.726 --> 02:22.349
Oh, but Chad, I had to
cancel the cable

02:22.383 --> 02:23.729
to afford
the trampoline.

02:23.764 --> 02:25.317
Oh.But I thought this
would be better!

02:25.352 --> 02:27.492
You know, it'll give us us fresh
air and exercise, you know?

02:27.526 --> 02:30.322
You mean,
we can jump on it too?

02:30.357 --> 02:32.152
[ All cheering ]

02:43.024 --> 02:45.026
[ Both panting ]

02:45.234 --> 02:47.374
[ Mary giggles ]
Mary: Come on, guys!

02:47.408 --> 02:49.583
This is a blast!

02:49.617 --> 02:52.379
[ Both laughing ]

02:52.413 --> 02:53.656
Cannonball!

02:53.690 --> 02:55.485
I have the coolest mom.

02:55.520 --> 02:56.693
Woo hoo hoo! Whoo!

02:56.728 --> 02:58.695
Your dinner's
getting cold!

02:58.730 --> 03:00.766
All right!
Just a minute!

03:00.801 --> 03:02.596
I've almost got
this flip down!

03:02.630 --> 03:03.769
[ Screams ]

03:03.804 --> 03:05.495
Mary!Mom!

03:05.530 --> 03:06.703
Got any Kings?

03:06.738 --> 03:08.188
Nope, go fish.

03:08.222 --> 03:09.775
All right.
[ Clears throat ]
Any Queens?

03:09.810 --> 03:11.605
Go fish.That's impossible.

03:11.639 --> 03:13.538
Okay, we've named
every card in the deck.

03:13.572 --> 03:15.505
Oh, really?

03:15.540 --> 03:16.955
All right, that's enough
Go Fish.

03:16.989 --> 03:18.198
Aw.

03:18.232 --> 03:19.371
How's that cast going?

03:19.406 --> 03:20.786
Sore.

03:20.821 --> 03:23.064
I just feel so silly
breaking my leg on a trampoline.

03:23.099 --> 03:26.620
Well...I'm gonna get this TV
working so you're not so bored.

03:26.654 --> 03:27.793
[ Grunting ]Anything?

03:27.828 --> 03:29.036
Uh...Anything?

03:29.070 --> 03:30.417
Do you know
what you're doing?

03:30.451 --> 03:31.625
Not really.

03:31.659 --> 03:33.385
Here we go --
public access!

03:33.420 --> 03:35.422
All right.
way to go Chad.

03:35.456 --> 03:37.631
Shoulder, shoulder.

03:37.665 --> 03:39.426
Jazz hands!

03:39.460 --> 03:40.634
Jazz hands!!

03:40.668 --> 03:42.049
Whoa ooh whoa
ooh whoa!

03:42.083 --> 03:43.257
This is TV?

03:43.292 --> 03:44.362
I think so.

03:44.396 --> 03:45.915
Jazz hands! Jazz hands!
Jazz hands!

03:45.949 --> 03:48.158
Jazz hands! Jazz hands!
Jazz hands!

03:48.193 --> 03:49.367
Whoa!

03:49.401 --> 03:51.783
You two are sweet, but you don't
have to entertain me.

03:51.817 --> 03:53.163
Go on jump
on the trampoline.

03:53.198 --> 03:54.613
You know,
someone should enjoy it.

03:54.648 --> 03:56.166
I can finally start
on this book...

03:56.201 --> 03:57.306
[ Giggling ]

03:57.340 --> 03:58.548
One, two, three!

03:58.583 --> 03:59.756
[ Screams ]

03:59.791 --> 04:01.724
All right.
Here we go.

04:01.758 --> 04:03.829
Chapter one --
trepidation.

04:03.864 --> 04:06.004
"A delitescent rapscallion
deturp--"

04:06.038 --> 04:07.177
[ Sighs ]

04:07.212 --> 04:08.662
"Deturpated."

04:08.696 --> 04:10.905
Okay, I know I know these
aren't real words.

04:10.940 --> 04:13.322
All right, world,
what have you got for me?

04:13.356 --> 04:14.771
Hmm.

04:14.806 --> 04:16.186
Been there. Hah.

04:16.221 --> 04:17.395
[ Laughs ]

04:17.429 --> 04:19.293
Oh! Ms. Mushburger's
packages.

04:21.364 --> 04:22.572
[ Whistles ]

04:22.607 --> 04:24.125
What a place.

04:24.160 --> 04:25.989
Okay.

04:26.024 --> 04:27.128
Strange.

04:27.163 --> 04:29.752
Ooh!
Now, that'sa beautiful setup!

04:29.786 --> 04:31.167
[ Panting, groans ]

04:31.201 --> 04:32.168
Ow, no, no.

04:32.202 --> 04:33.514
Ah, better rest
a second.

04:33.549 --> 04:35.033
[ Grunts ]

04:36.655 --> 04:38.312
Eh, why not?

04:38.347 --> 04:42.351
This has to be the brat-worst
thing to ever happen.

04:42.385 --> 04:43.800
Blegh.

04:43.835 --> 04:45.768
I'm telling ya, bud.
I hit the jackpot.

04:45.802 --> 04:47.321
Cha-ching![ Laughs ]

04:47.356 --> 04:49.219
Newscaster: Dentists --
Are they good for you?

04:49.254 --> 04:50.600
Your children --
Are they bad for you?

04:50.635 --> 04:52.015
[ Snickers ]

04:52.050 --> 04:53.223
Coming up
on the 6:00 o'clock news.

04:53.258 --> 04:55.191
[ Gasps ]
It's almost 6:00 already?

04:55.225 --> 04:56.641
[ Grunting ]

04:56.675 --> 04:57.849
Whew.

04:57.883 --> 04:59.057
Mom, we're back!

04:59.091 --> 05:00.507
Sorry we were gone
so long.

05:00.541 --> 05:01.715
We brought you back pizza,
through.

05:01.749 --> 05:03.164
And then,
I found this hat.

05:03.199 --> 05:04.649
It was super fun.

05:04.683 --> 05:06.375
You couldn't come
'cause of your leg.

05:06.409 --> 05:07.617
Sorry.

05:07.652 --> 05:09.378
Ah, it's fine, though.
I read my book.

05:09.412 --> 05:10.551
Oh, what's it about?

05:10.586 --> 05:12.035
Oh, uh, yes.

05:12.070 --> 05:15.384
Uh, it is...
It's about a, uh, man.

05:15.418 --> 05:16.626
[ Munching ]

05:16.661 --> 05:17.972
Wow.

05:18.007 --> 05:19.802
Uh, how 'bout some TV
with dinner, huh?

05:19.836 --> 05:21.217
[ Dialing ]

05:21.251 --> 05:22.218
Good evening.

05:22.252 --> 05:23.702
Man:
I'm calling you, man.

05:23.737 --> 05:24.910
Yeah, but why
you calling me?

05:24.945 --> 05:26.084
I saw you're number.

05:26.118 --> 05:27.361
Nah, peace.[ Phone hangs up ]

05:27.396 --> 05:28.742
Oh, okay,
what do we got?

05:28.776 --> 05:29.984
[ Phone dials ] Good evening.

05:30.019 --> 05:31.365
-Hi.
-Hello, honey.

05:31.400 --> 05:33.091
Woman: Yeah, uh...hey,
how's it, uh...

05:33.125 --> 05:35.093
Hey, we could watch TV
at Ms. Mushburger's.

05:35.127 --> 05:36.266
I got a key.

05:36.301 --> 05:37.406
Huh! You crazy?

05:37.440 --> 05:38.924
She'd definitely flip
if she found out

05:38.959 --> 05:40.374
we touched any
of her stuff.

05:40.409 --> 05:41.651
Witches hate that.

05:41.686 --> 05:43.688
[Chuckles nervously ]
Yeah, you're probably right.

05:43.722 --> 05:47.208
[ Panting ]

05:47.243 --> 05:48.831
[ Chad yawns ]

05:48.865 --> 05:50.936
Morning. Thought we'd go for
a car ride today, or --

05:50.971 --> 05:54.043
Actually, I-I think I'm just
gonna stay home and read,

05:54.077 --> 05:57.598
but if you're feeling super
helpful, I got these chores

05:57.633 --> 05:59.117
that need to get done.

05:59.151 --> 06:00.290
Oh. Okay.

06:00.325 --> 06:02.845
Uh, "dry cleaning,
car wash --"

06:02.879 --> 06:06.296
Yay! Chores!

06:06.331 --> 06:08.437
[ Tires screech ]

06:08.471 --> 06:10.093
[ Giggles ]

06:11.405 --> 06:14.132
Who knew going on two dates
at once would end up being

06:14.166 --> 06:16.410
a total pizzaaster?

06:16.445 --> 06:18.274
[ Mary laughs ]

06:19.931 --> 06:21.415
[ TV theme song plays ]

06:21.450 --> 06:23.003
[ Crashing ]

06:24.004 --> 06:27.179
[ Theme music continues ]

06:45.128 --> 06:46.923
German George:
And after our date,

06:46.958 --> 06:48.408
she said she was
thinking about

06:48.442 --> 06:49.995
becoming a
nihilist again.

06:50.030 --> 06:52.619
Now, that is
the brat-worst.

06:52.653 --> 06:54.483
[ Laughs ]
I get it now!

06:54.517 --> 06:55.725
[ Laughs ]

06:55.760 --> 06:57.347
Oh, shoot!

06:57.382 --> 06:59.764
Well, I think there is
a shower upstairs.

06:59.798 --> 07:01.282
[ Door closes ]Clarence: Hmm.

07:01.317 --> 07:03.181
Who do you think
it's from?

07:03.215 --> 07:04.734
Your mom.

07:04.769 --> 07:06.184
Oh.

07:06.218 --> 07:08.428
Want to jump
on the trampoline?

07:08.462 --> 07:10.844
[ Laughing ]

07:10.878 --> 07:13.433
Ah, nothing like
a hot bath to --

07:13.467 --> 07:14.503
[ Gasps ]

07:14.537 --> 07:16.125
[ Speaks indistinctly ]She's back! No!

07:16.159 --> 07:18.679
Wha! Ahh!
[ Grunts ]

07:18.714 --> 07:20.198
Shoot!

07:20.232 --> 07:21.855
She's gonna flip if she sees me
in her stuff.

07:21.889 --> 07:23.028
I got to hide.

07:23.063 --> 07:24.961
No, the flight
was fine.

07:24.996 --> 07:27.688
Oh. I have no recollection
of this piece.

07:27.723 --> 07:29.276
No, no.
Not you, Klause.

07:29.310 --> 07:30.277
[ Laughing ]

07:30.311 --> 07:31.658
[ Hushed ]
Psst! Hey, hey, hey!

07:31.692 --> 07:33.211
Mary, why are you
up there?

07:33.245 --> 07:34.626
Are -- are we
in the wrong yard?

07:34.661 --> 07:36.697
No. Chad, help.
I'm trapped.

07:36.732 --> 07:38.216
[ Door jostles ]Oh, I got to go.

07:38.250 --> 07:39.769
Chad, that witch
has got her!

07:39.804 --> 07:41.046
Oh, no! Oh, no!

07:41.081 --> 07:42.392
What do we do?
Should we call the police?

07:42.427 --> 07:44.360
Police can't stop
witches.

07:44.394 --> 07:46.707
We got to do it
ourselves.

07:46.742 --> 07:48.295
[ Dramatic music plays ]

07:48.329 --> 07:52.057
It's all here --
all the terror has landed.

07:52.092 --> 07:54.888
All right, so, I trampoline
bounce onto the witch's roof

07:54.922 --> 07:56.303
and enter
through the chimney.

07:56.337 --> 07:58.374
Hopefully, she's not the
"Hansel and Gretel" kind.

07:58.408 --> 07:59.824
Then what?

07:59.858 --> 08:01.653
I save her.

08:01.688 --> 08:03.034
Perfect plan.

08:03.068 --> 08:05.174
One more thing -- don't look
into the witch's eyes.

08:05.208 --> 08:07.176
That's how
she curses you.

08:07.210 --> 08:09.627
Now, let's go get my
mo-o-o-o-m-m-m--

08:09.661 --> 08:11.076
We're coming, Mary!

08:11.111 --> 08:14.148
Just to be clear, bud,

08:14.183 --> 08:15.529
you shouldn't ever do this --
not normally.

08:15.564 --> 08:16.910
Only if you're, like,

08:16.944 --> 08:18.359
going after a witch
that's getting at your mom.

08:18.394 --> 08:19.533
I know, I know.

08:19.568 --> 08:20.741
[ Grunts ]

08:20.776 --> 08:21.915
Ready?

08:21.949 --> 08:23.364
Almost...now!

08:23.399 --> 08:24.538
[ Grunts ]

08:24.573 --> 08:26.022
[ Yells ]

08:29.750 --> 08:30.993
[ Giggles ] What?

08:31.027 --> 08:32.581
Oh, I hope that's not
what I think.

08:32.615 --> 08:33.754
[ Sighs ]

08:33.789 --> 08:35.100
I really
must move, Klause.

08:35.135 --> 08:36.688
You would not believe
the neighbors.

08:36.723 --> 08:38.379
They're animals.
-Hey.

08:38.414 --> 08:40.002
Clarence:
I'm on the roof, Chad!

08:40.036 --> 08:41.831
Chad, look how high I am!
-No, no, no, no!

08:41.866 --> 08:43.557
I can see everything!

08:43.592 --> 08:46.215
There's Belson's house,
and the school,

08:46.249 --> 08:48.355
and the mountains,
and the sun...

08:48.389 --> 08:51.565
That's great, buddy,
but remember the plan.

08:51.600 --> 08:52.946
One second!

08:52.980 --> 08:54.948
...and the Earth,
and the galaxy.

08:54.982 --> 08:59.366
Okay, I-I'm gonna go
down the chimney now!

08:59.400 --> 09:00.470
[ Grunts ]

09:00.505 --> 09:03.439
Uh, Chad?
I think I'm stuck.

09:03.473 --> 09:05.303
[ Gasps ]How does Santa do it?

09:05.337 --> 09:07.547
I'll save you,
Clarence.

09:07.581 --> 09:08.996
[ Grunting ]

09:12.621 --> 09:14.208
Ah, yes,
it's all here.

09:14.243 --> 09:15.485
I'm giddy
with excitement.

09:15.520 --> 09:17.453
[ Gasps ][ Ms. Mushburger Chuckles ]

09:17.487 --> 09:19.144
[ Gasps ]

09:19.179 --> 09:21.491
Yeah, bye-bye. Mwah!

09:21.526 --> 09:22.700
Another? Okay!

09:22.734 --> 09:24.115
Mwah!

09:24.149 --> 09:28.222
[ Dramatic music plays ]

09:28.257 --> 09:30.431
[ Dramatic music stops ]

09:30.466 --> 09:32.088
What to wear?

09:32.123 --> 09:35.333
[ Mary grunts ]

09:35.367 --> 09:36.610
[ Gasps ]

09:39.786 --> 09:41.097
Mary?

09:41.132 --> 09:42.996
[ Screams ]

09:46.344 --> 09:47.690
[ Moans ]

09:49.658 --> 09:51.660
Mary? Mary?

09:51.694 --> 09:52.937
[ Moans ]

09:52.971 --> 09:55.422
[ Exhales ]
M-Ms. Mushburger.

09:55.456 --> 09:57.804
Please, don't curse me
o-or eat me.

09:57.838 --> 10:00.530
I don't know what you think
you saw, but this is

10:00.565 --> 10:03.464
a performance-art piece,
and it deserves to be seen

10:03.499 --> 10:05.605
in its
proper context.

10:05.639 --> 10:08.366
Wait. The cauldrons and --
and everything?

10:08.400 --> 10:10.679
It was just -- It was all
an art project?

10:10.713 --> 10:11.921
Yah, yah.

10:11.956 --> 10:13.751
It's high art,
avant-garde.

10:13.785 --> 10:15.166
You wouldn't understand.

10:15.200 --> 10:18.341
Huh! Well, I-I feel like
a real dummy over here.

10:18.376 --> 10:21.103
And let's not forget that you've
broken into my house,

10:21.137 --> 10:23.692
so you will leave now,
and I will be taking this.

10:23.726 --> 10:25.038
Goodbye.

10:25.072 --> 10:26.556
Now, remember --
don't look her in the eyes.

10:26.591 --> 10:28.041
[ Doorknob jostles ]The witch!

10:28.075 --> 10:29.767
Remember the plan!
Remember the plan!

10:29.801 --> 10:31.561
[ Screaming ]

10:31.596 --> 10:34.047
We have a petition
for you to sign.

10:34.081 --> 10:36.394
Give us back my mom!

10:37.809 --> 10:39.846
I think my other leg
is broken.

10:39.880 --> 10:41.054
Oof.

10:41.088 --> 10:42.365
Aw, dip.

10:42.400 --> 10:44.160
[ Insects chirping ][ Chad snores ]

10:44.195 --> 10:47.060
Mom, are your legs
ever gonna heal?

10:47.094 --> 10:49.234
Careful, Clarence.
They're still tender.

10:49.269 --> 10:51.892
[ Howling on TV ] Ooh-hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

10:51.927 --> 10:53.549
[ Laughs ]

10:53.583 --> 10:58.727
Boys and ghouls, only 200 days
left till Halloween!

10:58.761 --> 10:59.900
[ Laughs ]

10:59.935 --> 11:01.868
Pfft. High art.
Yeah, right.

11:01.902 --> 11:03.593
Told you she was
a witch.

11:06.010 --> 11:07.011
♪ Early to bed

11:08.702 --> 11:11.118
♪ Early to rise

11:12.568 --> 11:14.708
♪ Picking my nose
